>> REGINA: Yes, it is.

01:01:58.800 --> 01:01:59.640 align:middle line:90%
Any final thoughts?

01:01:59.640 --> 01:02:02.630 align:middle line:84%
We only have about
one minute left?

01:02:02.630 --> 01:02:05.090 align:middle line:84%
>> SHELDRAKE: Well, the
main thing is that all these

01:02:05.090 --> 01:02:08.535 align:middle line:84%
practices that I write
about are open to everyone.

01:02:08.535 --> 01:02:10.160 align:middle line:90%
They're inclusive.

01:02:10.160 --> 01:02:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And they're not
things where you have

01:02:12.380 --> 01:02:15.710 align:middle line:84%
to start by believing or
signing up to something.

01:02:15.710 --> 01:02:18.320 align:middle line:84%
They're all based
on experience first.

01:02:18.320 --> 01:02:20.720 align:middle line:90%
Practice leading to experience.

01:02:20.720 --> 01:02:22.970 align:middle line:10%
And I myself think the
root of all religions

01:02:22.970 --> 01:02:25.370 align:middle line:10%
is an experience,
first and foremost.

01:02:25.370 --> 01:02:27.830 align:middle line:10%
The doctrines come along later.

01:02:27.830 --> 01:02:30.810 align:middle line:10%
But all the great religions
start from direct experience.

01:02:30.810 --> 01:02:33.130 align:middle line:10%
Buddha's enlightenment
under a tree;

01:02:33.130 --> 01:02:37.680 align:middle line:10%
Jesus' experience of being a
direct connection with God;

01:02:37.680 --> 01:02:40.250 align:middle line:10%
Muhammad's experience
of the voice

01:02:40.250 --> 01:02:43.250 align:middle line:10%
of God speaking through him.

01:02:43.250 --> 01:02:45.650 align:middle line:10%
They all start with experience.

01:02:45.650 --> 01:02:48.380 align:middle line:10%
And that, I think,
is the starting point

01:02:48.380 --> 01:02:49.790 align:middle line:10%
for all spiritual life.

01:02:49.790 --> 01:02:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And I think that by looking
at the spiritual experiences,

01:02:53.390 --> 01:02:56.130 align:middle line:84%
which are part of all
religious traditions,

01:02:56.130 --> 01:02:59.420 align:middle line:84%
we can reconnect
through our own practice

01:02:59.420 --> 01:03:01.830 align:middle line:90%
through these experiences.

01:03:01.830 --> 01:03:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And we can then either continue
to do them just individually,

01:03:05.040 --> 01:03:07.550 align:middle line:84%
or we can join together
with other people, which is

01:03:07.550 --> 01:03:09.860 align:middle line:90%
in itself a spiritual practice.

01:03:09.860 --> 01:03:10.670 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Indeed.

01:03:10.670 --> 01:03:13.820 align:middle line:84%
There is a part of us that
has this innate connection

01:03:13.820 --> 01:03:17.570 align:middle line:84%
to the all, the great mystery,
and when we cut ourselves off

01:03:17.570 --> 01:03:20.769 align:middle line:84%
from it, you can't help but
feel just a little bit grayer.

01:03:20.769 --> 01:03:21.810 align:middle line:90%
>> SHELDRAKE: Definitely.

01:03:21.810 --> 01:03:22.760 align:middle line:90%
And more depressed.

01:03:22.760 --> 01:03:23.810 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And a
little more depressed.

01:03:23.810 --> 01:03:24.830 align:middle line:90%
And that's been proven.

01:03:24.830 --> 01:03:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And your book is helping
people find their way

01:03:27.260 --> 01:03:29.490 align:middle line:84%
back to something
that works for them.

01:03:29.490 --> 01:03:31.371 align:middle line:90%
It's not dogmatic in any way.

01:03:31.371 --> 01:03:33.620 align:middle line:84%
It's finding your way to the
things that work for you,

01:03:33.620 --> 01:03:35.660 align:middle line:84%
like singing, and
gratitude, and love,

01:03:35.660 --> 01:03:38.300 align:middle line:84%
and appreciation, which
